.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-ARPRULES 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.11.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-arprules \- ARP packet filtering rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I arprules
file defines ARP packet filtering rules.  The compiler emits these rules
into a separate
.B arp shorewall
nft table (ARP family), which is distinct from the main
.I inet shorewall
table used for IP traffic.

Use
.I arprules
to prevent ARP spoofing or to restrict which hosts may send ARP replies on
a given interface.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/arprules
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	ACCEPT or DROP
SOURCE	yes	Source IP address or CIDR (or - for any)
DEST	yes	Destination IP address or CIDR (or - for any)
INTERFACE	no	Interface filter
MAC	no	Source MAC address filter
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Allow ARP only from known subnets on the local interface:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  SOURCE           DEST  INTERFACE
ACCEPT   192.168.1.0/24   -     eth1
DROP     -                -     eth1
.fi
.RE
.PP
Allow ARP from a specific MAC address:
.RS
.nf
ACCEPT   -   -   eth1   00:11:22:33:44:55
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-interfaces (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-maclist (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)

